### ESLint version

8.36.0

### What problem do you want to solve?

ESLint spends several whole seconds on projects with many entries dealing with node_modules (preparing caches, checking for config files, and iterating each of the second level subdirectories to match the ignore pattern). Even on projects with no dev dependencies besides ESLint (eslint-config-wikimedia: 0.24.0), it still makes up ~2 seconds as there are by default ~170 flattened subdirectories.

This is due to the default ignore pattern being `/**/node_modules/*` rather than `/**/node_modules/`. The trailing star means that the glob matcher "needs" to enter and match each subdir as it cannot match the first-level directory itself.

I suspect this got worse over the years as npm moved toward flattening node_modules, which it didn't before a few years ago.


